commit.message:
Require both TBB_FIND_PACKAGE and TBB_DIR for external TBB usage(#1324)

Currently TBB attempts a find package and excludes the entire build part of the CMake setup when *either* `TBB_FIND_PACKAGE` *or* `TBB_DIR` are defined. This is an issue when using `FetchContent` with `OVERRIDE_FIND_PACKAGE` as CMake declares `TBB_DIR` to equal `${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/CMakeFiles/pkgRedirects/`.

verification.payload:
tree c42013f9faf5367c388a40da9a582271d035a1fe
parent df7306cb1e2605dac5fc4a8361b4e617f6bf79a6
author Daniel Simon <dansimon09@gmail.com> 1710415887 -0700
committer GitHub <noreply@github.com> 1710415887 +0100

Require both TBB_FIND_PACKAGE and TBB_DIR for external TBB usage(#1324)

Currently TBB attempts a find package and excludes the entire build part of the CMake setup when *either* `TBB_FIND_PACKAGE` *or* `TBB_DIR` are defined. This is an issue when using `FetchContent` with `OVERRIDE_FIND_PACKAGE` as CMake declares `TBB_DIR` to equal `${CMAKE_BINARY_DIR}/CMakeFiles/pkgRedirects/`.

commit.message:
Fix deadlock in test_scheduler_mix (#1309)

After stealing, current arena must be taken into account while selecting
next arena to prevent deadlock. Arena index is passed explicitly for that.
